## Part 0: Development Workflow (1 hour)

### 0.1 Git Workflow

```bash
# Make sure you're on main and up to date
git checkout main
git pull origin main

# Create feature branch (use descriptive name)
git checkout -b feat/my-feature-description

# Make changes
# Edit files, add code, write tests

# Stage changes
git add module/user/handler.go module/user/handler_test.go

# Commit with clear message
git commit -m "Add user search endpoint

- Implements GET /users/search?q=<query>
- Filters by tenant_id for security
- Returns paginated results
- Includes unit and integration tests"

# Push to remote
git push -u origin feat/my-feature-description

# Create PR on GitHub
gh pr create --fill
# Or go to GitHub and create PR from the branch
```

### 0.2 Commit Message Convention

```
# Good: Clear, describes what and why
git commit -m "Add user search endpoint

Implements full-text search for users in a tenant.
Addresses feature request #42."

# Bad: Vague
git commit -m "Fix stuff"
git commit -m "Update user module"
git commit -m "WIP"
```

